cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.HC 

This paper focuses on the interdependency between human mobility and social proximity, and the influence of social networks on enhancing location prediction of an individual. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also investigates the transmission of social trends/influences within social networks, which falls under the sub-category cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences). Additionally, the paper uses a large dataset and applies machine learning techniques to predict human mobility, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper also discusses the traits of personality and their impact on mobility behavior, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
